The percentage of VS degraded during the AD process (Fig. 3) accounted for 13, 71, and 24% for raw AS, SCG, and HS, respectively. The pretreatment with 73% NMMO significantly (p < 0.05) enhanced the VS biodegradation of AS up to 21%. On the other hand, no significant difference (p > 0.05) was observed in VS degraded from raw and pretreated SCG. Regarding HS, all pretreatment durations considerably increased the amount of biodegradable matter (p < 0.05), with the increment being positively correlated with the pretreatment time and reaching 54% in the case of 5 h NMMO pretreatment.Fig. 3
